observations.recommendation:
1. Use the inventory working papers provided by the General Service Office (GSO) as basis for inventory taking activities, taking into consideration the capitalization threshold of ₱15,000.00;
2. Record/document the daily physical count in a standard Inventory Count Form (ICF), which shall be used as the basis in the preparation of the RPCPPE after the physical count;
3. Tag all PPE items counted with new property stickers containing the information provided by the said Circular;
4. State clearly in the ICF the PPEs’ condition, found at station and not found during the physical count which described as “non-existing” or “missing”, as well as other relevant information of each PPE; and
5. Prepare the RPCPPE upon completion of the physical count.

