We recommended that the following courses of actions be made by the LGU Local Chief Executive, to wit:
a. Direct the LGU Accountant:
1. To secure the monthly bank statement from its authorized government depository bank (AGDB) for all their bank accounts maintained and then prepare the monthly bank reconciliation statements for each bank accounts in accordance with Section 74 of PD No. 1445 and Section 3.2 of COA Circular No. 96-011;
2. To conduct in-depth review once at each annual reporting date the residual value and the useful life of an asset upon recognition of depreciable amount of each lug’s property, plant and equipment;
3. To prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component of Road Network account at the end of the year;
4. To maintain a subsidiary record particularly Property Ledger Cards (PLC) for property, plant and equipment accounts and Local Road Network Ledger Card for local road network and its components; and
5. To take the necessary adjustments noted in the books of accounts by drawing a Journal Entry Voucher (JEV);
b. Direct the Local Inventory Committee to continue the conduct of a physical count of all equipment belonging to their respective offices; and (2) then to submit a complete Annual Physical Inventory of all property under the agency control as of 31, December, on General Form (41) not later than 31 January of each year;
c. Require the LGU General Services Officer to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map; and
d. Direct the Municipal Engineer to provide the local accountant and the general services officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

