We recommended that the concerned LGU top officials make the necessary step for the complete recognition of Local Road Network in the books of accounts as provided in the said circular, such as:
Conduct an inventory of the local roads under the LGU’s jurisdiction;
Maintain the following records/reports: Report of the Local Road Network (RLRN), Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Network (RPCLRN), Local Road Network Ledger Card (LRNLC), and Local Road Network Property Card (LRNPC);
Make the necessary adjusting entries in the books upon recognition of Local Road Network account.

It is recommended that the management should initiate measures designed to come up with a Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) with the GSIS defining therein the agreed balance of payables to GSIS, if any, and the terms and conditions in the settlement thereof.  The following steps may help in facilitating reconciliation of records, to wit:

Secure detailed profile of payables per GSIS records;
Reconstruct old GSIS accounts, if necessary, and update records;
Reconstruct old personnel profile, if necessary, and update personnel profile;
Counter-check GSIS records with the reconstructed and updated accounting and personnel records of the LGU; 
Negotiate with the GSIS for any differences that may be noted during counter-checking activity;
Enter into a formal agreement with the GSIS in the form of a Memorandum of Agreement (MOA); and
Appropriate fund for the settlement of any payables to the GSIS as agreed in the MOA.
